h3. Issue Summary

When trying to use the *Create Linked Issue* in a Jira Software board, the page reloads and nothing happens.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a Jira Service Desk project and an issue;
# Create a Jira Software Classic project (Kanban or Scrum board);
# Update the Jira Software board filter to include the Jira Service Desk issue;
# Select the Jira Service Desk issue in the Board or Backlog;
# Press "." and type *Create Linked Issues* and press enter.

h3. Expected Results

The *Create Linked Issues* pop-up window to be displayed

h3. Actual Results

The page refreshes and the following errors occur in the console:

{code}
Request URL: https://{instanceURL}rest/api/2/issue/ST-10/properties/tss_s3_issue?&_r=1560446312202
Request Method: GET
Status Code: 404 
Remote Address: 18.234.32.175:443
Referrer Policy: no-referrer-when-downgrade
{code}


{code}
Request URL: https://{instanceURL}rest/greenhopper/1.0/xboard/work/allData.json?rapidViewId=NaN&selectedProjectKey=IK&_=1560446309692
Request Method: GET
Status Code: 404 
Remote Address: 18.234.32.175:443
Referrer Policy: no-referrer-when-downgrade
{code}

h3. Notes

* As this is a Jira Service Desk feature, this is expected to not work in Jira Software projects. However, this should either;
* Not display the *Create Linked Issue* option when accessing the issue in a Jira Software project or;
* Open the pop-up window as expected.

h3. Workaround

Open the issue in another window and use the *Created Linked Issue* feature.

{panel:title=Bug Fix Policy|titleBGColor=#e0efff}
