 At the moment, we can't set an ETA for the fix to be released, since there's a number of factors that determine how our product team prioritizes bugfixes.
 You can learn more by reading [Atlassian Cloud Bug Fixing Policy|https://confluence.atlassian.com/support/atlassian-cloud-bug-fixing-policy-206865884.html].
{panel}
h3. Issue Summary

REST API [POST /rest/api/3/group/user|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/#api-rest-api-3-group-user-post] responses an internal server error when portal-only user is specified.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a customer account on JSD
 # Retrieve the customer's Atlassian ID via [GET /rest/api/3/user/search|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/?utm_source=%2Fcloud%2Fjira%2Fplatform%2Frest%2F&utm_medium=302#api-rest-api-3-user-picker-get]
 # Perform the request with specifying the customer account
 ** Sample script: [^sample.bash]

h3. Expected Results

The endpoint responses 4xx error and clarify the portal-only user cannot be added to groups.
h3. Actual Results

The endpoint responses 500 error with the body below:
{code:javascript}
{
  "errorMessages": [
    "Internal server error"
  ],
  "errors": {}
}
{code}
h3. Workaround

None. Consider adding yourself as a watcher to be kept informed as to the state of the bug moving forward. With that way, if our development team updates the ticket, you'll be notified via email.
